# .pddignore — paths the PDD puzzle scanner (`npm run puzzles`) skips.
# One glob per line (pdd --exclude syntax); blank lines and '#' comments ignored.
#
# Real puzzle markers are tracked everywhere NOT listed here. When a scanned
# (code) file only *refers to* the marker keyword rather than declaring a real
# puzzle, use the lowercase placeholder at_todo — see docs/claude_workflow.md
# for the reason. The scanner is a dumb, case-sensitive substring matcher: it
# trips on the UPPERCASE keyword even inside a larger token, so the placeholder
# MUST be lowercase to stay invisible to the scan.

# --- not our source / generated / repo copies ---
node_modules/**
.claude/**
coverage/**
package-lock.json

# --- fixtures, throwaway, experiment/illustrative collections ---
tests/goldens/**
scratch/**
experiments/**
public_experiments/**

# --- the scanner itself: its source must contain the literal marker to work ---
scripts/puzzle-status.js

# --- generated velocity dataset: copies the CSV notes column verbatim, which
#     quotes the keyword while *describing* PDD mechanics (not real puzzles).
#     The real stats puzzle lives in stats/enrich.py (a scanned .py file). ---
stats/*.csv

# --- this ignore-file: it is config, not source (and the wrapper feeds it in) ---
.pddignore

# --- markdown: saturated with natural-English uppercase mentions of the
#     keyword; the few real doc-puzzles are GitHub-tracked instead ---
docs/**
*.md
